1. FTX starts the second phase of repayment process, and it is expected to issue more than $5 billion starting today;
2. After multiple rounds of liquidation and stop loss, James Wynn has only $800,000 left of the $3.25 million he collected yesterday;
3. REX Shares submitted Solana and Ethereum pledge ETF prospectus, and is expected to be listed in the United States within a few weeks;
4. Cetus plans to complete full recovery and restart in about a week;
5. Orange Cap Games announced that it has acquired Moonbirds, Mythics and Oddities from Yuga Labs;
6. Atticus, a stablecoin company co-founded by former Circle executives, is about to complete a new round of financing, with a valuation of $1.5-2 billion;
8. The New York City Comptroller vetoed the Bitcoin municipal bond plan;
9. SEC Commissioner Peirce: Meme tokens such as TRUMP are not within the scope of SEC regulatory protection.
